     * ECSS AROUND THE WORLD
          + Regional Economic, Social and Environmental Councils
          + The European Economic and Social Committee
          + Online cooperation between Economic & Social Councils in the
            EU (CESlink)
          + The International Association of Economic and Social Councils
            and Similar Institutions (AICESIS)

   The Economic, Social and Environmental Council (ESEC) is a
   constitutional consultative assembly. It represents key economic,
   social and environmental fields, promoting cooperation between
   different socio-professional interest groups and ensuring they are part
   of the process of shaping and reviewing public policy.

Methods of referral

   Methods of referral

Referral process

   Referral process
   View ESEC overview

